# Homelab Goose Agent Hints
# Injected into every Goose session as persistent context.

## Key Patterns
- Use conventional commits: feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|build|ci|chore
- Container images use apko (not Dockerfiles) — always dual-arch (x86_64 + aarch64)
- Non-root containers: uid 65532, runAsNonRoot: true
- Secrets via 1Password Operator (OnePasswordItem CRD) — never hardcode
- Run `format` to regenerate BUILD files after Go/Python source changes

## GitHub
- Use `gh` CLI for all GitHub operations (PRs, issues, API calls)
- GITHUB_TOKEN is pre-configured in the environment

## Cluster Access
- DO NOT use kubectl get/describe/logs/top — use MCP tools via Context Forge
- DO NOT use argocd CLI — use MCP tools
- Allowed kubectl: explain, api-resources, port-forward, exec, cp, run

## Build System
- Bazel runs remotely via BuildBuddy CI — not locally
- Python deps: @pip//package (aspect_rules_py, not rules_python)
- JS deps: pnpm + rules_js
- Bazel deps: bzlmod (MODULE.bazel), not WORKSPACE

## GitOps
- Services live in projects/<service>/deploy/ with application.yaml + values.yaml
- To change cluster state: edit values.yaml → commit → push → ArgoCD auto-syncs
- NEVER use kubectl apply/patch/edit/scale/delete

## Output Formatting
Your output is rendered as markdown in a dashboard UI. Use markdown formatting
(headers, lists, code blocks) for clarity. Do not include raw terminal output
like progress bars or spinner characters.
